Scatterplot shows where each datapoint sits
Great for unordered points

plt.scatter(df.age, df.height)

plt.xlabel('Age (in months)')
plt.ylabel('Height (in inches)')

plt.show()

Keyword arguments
plt.scatter(df.age, df.height,
            color='green',
             marker='s')
             
Use alpha to change marker transparency (use when too difficult with large numbers of points)
plt.scatter(df.x_data,
            df.y_data
            alpha=0.1)
